  <entry>
    <title>Real life is where context gets hard</title>
    <link href="https://hunyuan.tencent.com/research/100039"/>
    <id>ecc7d798389ec84432cdd0535851d1f9</id>
    <published>2026-04-30T07:00:00+00:00</published>
    <updated>2026-04-30T07:00:00+00:00</updated>
    <summary type="text">Previously, we built CL-Bench to test whether AI could learn complex new knowledge, such as rules, and use it effectively. But real life doesn't come with a rulebook. To be a helpful everyday assistant, an AI must do more than just understand complex rules; it should also understand complex human relationships and piece together clues from messy, scattered context.</summary>
